# Project: Knovie (知频) — Video Knowledge Base

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui)
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/google`) with Gemini 2.5 Flash
- **Backend**: Python 3.11+ FastAPI (async) for crawling & transcription
- **Database**: SQLite (dev) → PostgreSQL (prod), accessed via better-sqlite3 (JS) / aiosqlite (Python)
- **Crawling**: bilibili-api-python (Bilibili), yt-dlp (YouTube)
- **Transcription**: subtitle-first → Groq Whisper API → Qwen-ASR → local faster-whisper

## Project Structure
```
knovie/
├── app/                        # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── api/chat/route.ts       # Vercel AI SDK streaming chat
│   ├── api/topics/route.ts     # Topic CRUD
│   ├── api/videos/route.ts     # Video list/search
│   ├── api/collect/route.ts    # Proxy to Python backend
│   ├── chat/page.tsx
│   ├── explore/page.tsx
│   ├── collect/page.tsx
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── page.tsx                # Dashboard
├── components/
│   ├── chat/                   # Chat UI components
│   ├── explorer/               # Video/Creator browsing
│   ├── collector/              # Crawl control panel
│   └── ui/                     # shadcn/ui base components
├── lib/
│   ├── db.ts                   # Database access layer
│   ├── ai.ts                   # Gemini agent config + tools
│   ├── types.ts                # Shared TypeScript types
│   └── utils.ts                # Helpers
├── backend/                    # Python FastAPI service
│   ├── main.py                 # FastAPI entry
│   ├── routers/                # API route modules
│   ├── lib/                    # scraper, db, transcriber
│   ├── handlers/               # bilibili_handler, youtube_handler
│   ├── services/               # ASR services
│   └── requirements.txt
└── .env.local
```

## Code Conventions

### TypeScript / Next.js
- Use functional components with hooks, never class components
- Use `"use client"` directive only when needed (hooks, event handlers, browser APIs)
- Prefer Server Components by default
- Use Vercel AI SDK `useChat` for chat interfaces, never raw fetch for streaming
- Use `zod` for all schema validation (API params, tool params)
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- Always define types in `lib/types.ts`, import from there
- Use `@/` path alias for imports

### Python / FastAPI
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- Use Pydantic v2 models for request/response schemas
- Use dependency injection for database sessions
- Error handling: never let exceptions crash the server, always return structured errors
- Logging: use `loguru` or structured logging, never bare `print()`

### Database
- All DB operations go through a DAO/repository layer, never raw SQL in route handlers
- Use parameterized queries, never string interpolation
- Keep SQLite for dev, design schema to be Postgres-compatible (no SQLite-only features except FTS5)

### UI / Styling
- Use shadcn/ui components as base, customize with Tailwind
- Dark mode support from day 1 (use CSS variables)
- Responsive: mobile-first
- Loading states for all async operations
- Toast notifications for errors and success via sonner

### AI / Chat
- System prompt includes topic context + available knowledge summary
- Tools must return JSON-serializable results
- maxSteps: 5 for multi-tool agent loops
- Always show tool call status in chat UI (searching, fetching, etc.)
